column5: Description
Command to turn the inverter On
Command for turning inverter Off
Command for transferring the output from inverter operation to Static Bypass operation
Command for transferring the output from Static Bypass operation to Inverter operation

The purpose of this register is to convey the mode of operation of the UPS at macro level.  It primarily indicates the power flow of the system  is it from mains  bypass  battery or not powerinfg the output.
column12: {"STATE_ONLINE": [0, "Indicates that the power for the output is being sourced from input, and delivery through the inverter" ],"STATE_BATTERY": [1,"Indicates that the power for the output is being sourced from the battery (or other energy storage) and delivered through the inverter"],"STATE_BYPASS": [2, "Indicates that the output is being powered by the input without being processed by the inverter" ],"STATE_OFF": [3,"Indicates that the output is not powered through the UPS (including any internal bypass paths.)" ] }

column5: Additional information to get the correct UPS status
column12: {"NO_MODIFIER": [0, "No modifier"],"FAULT": [1, "Indicates that a fault of any severity (warning, or critical) is present in the system, which may influence the UPS Mode"],"TEST": [2, "Indicates that a test is in progress"],"COMMANDED": [3, "Indicates that operation mode is caused by a user request"],"MAINTENANCE": [4, "Indicates the wrap around bypass breaker is activated, and UPS is locked in bypass operation"],"HIGH_EFFICIENCY":  [5,"Indicates that the UPS operates in high efficiency mode"],"FAULT_STATE": [6, "Modifier - indicates that the UPS is operating in a fault state."],"STATIC_BYPASS_STANDBY ": [7, "Modifier - The UPS has a fault and is ready to enter static bypass but awaits permission from the system. UPS output is off. Mode used for advanced battery operation management in parallel operation."],"INVESTER_STANDBY": [8, "Modifier - The UPS has a Mains 1 fault and is ready to enter battery operation but awaits permission from the system. UPS output is off. Mode used for advanced battery operation management in parallel operation."] }

column5: This is the configured AC voltage system setting. The setting applies for input as well  if no specific seeting is placed in InputSystem.

Ramp in timer for mains current limitation during transfer from Battery to online operation

Number of seconds elapsed since January 1st 2000. Conversion from date and time must be corrected for leap years. In UTC leap seconds are also defined  but these are ignored here when converting. Typically this is the local time where the device is installed.
Defines the AC wiring of the system  3 Wire  does not include neutral  where 4 wire is including neutral
column12: {"THREE_WIRE":[0, "3 wire system configuration"],"FOUR_WIRE":[1, "4 wire system configuration"]}
